    <p>The column that matters most for families managing unpredictable behavior is the cost-with-severity row. Traditional ABA billing scales directly with service intensity — more challenging weeks mean more sessions, which means a higher bill precisely when household stress is already elevated. A fixed subscription doesn't work that way. Families don't face a financial penalty during high-meltdown periods, which is where the structural difference between the two models becomes most tangible.</p>

