    <div class="tip-box">
      <span class="tip-label">Practical tip</span>
      Review your ROI data at 30-day intervals, not just at the end of a program. A downward trend in meltdown frequency that starts flattening at week 8 may signal that the program has addressed the easiest-to-shift triggers and that additional clinical support is now needed for the remaining ones. Catching that inflection point early — rather than running a 12-month program and discovering the gains plateaued at month 2 — is what makes structured data tracking the most financially valuable habit a family can build.
